<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Commercial Banking (GCB) is the leading commercial bank in the U.S., serving one out of three companies with revenues of between $2.5 million and several billion dollars.  Global Commercial Banking (GCB) generates more than $10 billion in annual revenue and $4 billion in net income from a variety of market-leading businesses. It serves more than 100,000 business banking and more than 30,000 middle-market clients through dedicated client teams who provide seamless, integrated delivery of the bank&#39;s full capabilities. GCB associates offer clients unrivaled market access, flexibility and value from their banking relationship through our core businesses.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>

<p class="bac">
The Global Commercial Banking MBA Leadership Program is designed to accomplish two goals; accelerate the growth needed to be successful in a client-facing role and develop future leaders for our businesses. The leadership program is comprised of credit, treasury management and client management process training. Lines of businesses include Global Commercial Banking, Large Corporate Treasury and Financial Institutions, and Leasing.  Associates in this program develop the skills and experience needed to accelerate their Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America career.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Leadership program candidates must have a MBA degree plus a minimum of three (3) years client-facing experience with direct focus on clients and a demonstrated record of achievement. (Financial services preferable)</li>
	<li>Candidates should have deep and broad finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, and strong personal leadership skills</li>
	<li>Candidates must be geographically flexible both at the beginning and at the end of the program. Permanent placement is determined by current business needs</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac" style="margin-left: 18px; margin-top: 12px;">Candidate Profile:</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA or equivalent graduate degree from an accredited college or university</li>
	<li>3-5  years of work experience prior to entering graduate school (Financial services preferable)</li>
	<li>Strong leadership and communication skills</li>
	<li>Ability to understand, navigate and thrive in a matrixed environment/organization</li>
	<li>Previous client-facing experience with direct focus on clients</li>
	<li>Geographic flexibility</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The training component of the leadership program consists of classroom, virtual and web-based courses. Throughout the program, formal training is combined with on-the-job activities designed to apply knowledge of technical, analytical, and relationship management skills.  During the program, each associate is given a support network, to provide coaching and feedback.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Positions are available in major markets across the Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America footprint. Line of business and location assignment is based on business need and candidate interest. Geographic flexibility is required at the end of the program in an effort to fill business critical roles across our footprint.
</p>

